#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.243"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.243:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.243:0.2"
msgid "25. Āpattibhayavagga"
msgstr "25. Perils of Offenses"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: pāpabhikkhusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.243:0.3"
msgid "243. Saṅghabhedakasutta"
msgstr "243. Schism in the Saṅgha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.243:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "an4.243:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "an4.243:1.3"
msgid "“api nu taṃ, ānanda, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantan”ti?"
msgstr "“Well, Ānanda, has that disciplinary issue been settled yet?”"

#. VAR: vūpasamissati → vūpasammissati (?)
msgctxt "an4.243:1.4"
msgid "“Kuto taṃ, bhante, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamissati."
msgstr "“How could it be, sir?"

msgctxt "an4.243:1.5"
msgid ""
"Āyasmato, bhante, anuruddhassa bāhiyo nāma saddhivihāriko kevalakappaṃ "
"saṃghabhedāya ṭhito."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Anuruddha’s pupil Bāhiya remains entirely committed to creating a "
"schism in the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an4.243:1.6"
msgid "Tatrāyasmā anuruddho na ekavācikampi bhaṇitabbaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "But Anuruddha doesn’t think to say a single word about it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: adhikaraṇesu → adhikaraṇesu tesu (mr)
msgctxt "an4.243:2.1"
msgid "“Kadā panānanda, anuruddho saṃghamajjhe adhikaraṇesu voyuñjati."
msgstr ""
"“But Ānanda, since when has Anuruddha been involved in disciplinary issues "
"in the midst of the Saṅgha?"

msgctxt "an4.243:2.2"
msgid ""
"Nanu, ānanda, yāni kānici adhikaraṇāni uppajjanti, sabbāni tāni tumhe ceva "
"vūpasametha sāriputtamoggallānā ca."
msgstr ""
"Shouldn’t you, together with Sāriputta and Moggallāna, settle all "
"disciplinary issues that come up?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.243:3.1"
msgid ""
"Cattārome, ānanda, atthavase sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena nandati."
msgstr "A bad monk sees four reasons to relish schism in the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an4.243:3.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.243:3.3"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, pāpabhikkhu dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo asuci saṅkassarasamācāro "
"paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño "
"antopūti avassuto kasambujāto."
msgstr ""
"Take an unethical monk, of bad qualities, filthy, with suspicious behavior, "
"underhand, no true ascetic or spiritual practitioner—though claiming to be "
"one—rotten inside, corrupt, and depraved."

msgctxt "an4.243:3.4"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an4.243:3.5"
msgid "‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—"
msgstr "‘Suppose the monks know that I’m a bad monk …"

msgctxt "an4.243:3.6"
msgid ""
"dussīlo pāpadhammo asuci saṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo "
"samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujātoti, "
"samaggā maṃ santā nāsessanti;"
msgstr "If they’re in harmony, they’ll expel me,"

msgctxt "an4.243:3.7"
msgid "vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti."
msgstr "but if they’re divided they won’t.’"

msgctxt "an4.243:3.8"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, ānanda, paṭhamaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena "
"nandati."
msgstr ""
"A bad monk sees this as the first reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.243:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, antaggāhikāya "
"diṭṭhiyā samannāgato."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a bad monk has wrong view, he’s attached to an extremist view."

msgctxt "an4.243:4.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an4.243:4.3"
msgid "‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—"
msgstr "‘Suppose the monks know that I have wrong view …"

msgctxt "an4.243:4.4"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhiko antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgatoti, samaggā maṃ santā "
"nāsessanti;"
msgstr "If they’re in harmony they’ll expel me,"

msgctxt "an4.243:4.5"
msgid "vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti."
msgstr "but if they’re divided they won’t.’"

msgctxt "an4.243:4.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, ānanda, dutiyaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena "
"nandati."
msgstr ""
"A bad monk sees this as the second reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.243:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu micchāājīvo hoti, micchāājīvena jīvikaṃ "
"kappeti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a bad monk has wrong livelihood and earns a living by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "an4.243:5.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an4.243:5.3"
msgid "‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—"
msgstr "‘Suppose the monks know that I have wrong livelihood …"

msgctxt "an4.243:5.4"
msgid ""
"micchāājīvo micchāājīvena jīvikaṃ kappetīti, samaggā maṃ santā nāsessanti;"
msgstr "If they’re in harmony they’ll expel me,"

msgctxt "an4.243:5.5"
msgid "vaggā pana maṃ na nāsessantī’ti."
msgstr "but if they’re divided they won’t.’"

msgctxt "an4.243:5.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, ānanda, tatiyaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṃghabhedena "
"nandati."
msgstr ""
"A bad monk sees this as the third reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.243:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, pāpabhikkhu lābhakāmo hoti sakkārakāmo anavaññattikāmo."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a bad monk desires material possessions, honor, and admiration."

msgctxt "an4.243:6.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an4.243:6.3"
msgid "‘sace kho maṃ bhikkhū jānissanti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose the monks know that I desire material possessions, honor, and "
"admiration."

msgctxt "an4.243:6.4"
msgid ""
"lābhakāmo sakkārakāmo anavaññattikāmoti, samaggā maṃ santā na sakkarissanti "
"na garuṃ karissanti na mānessanti na pūjessanti;"
msgstr ""
"If they’re in harmony they won’t honor, respect, revere, or venerate me,"

msgctxt "an4.243:6.5"
msgid "vaggā pana maṃ sakkarissanti garuṃ karissanti mānessanti pūjessantī’ti."
msgstr "but if they’re divided they will.’"

msgctxt "an4.243:6.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, ānanda, catutthaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena "
"nandati."
msgstr ""
"A bad monk sees this as the fourth reason to relish schism in the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an4.243:6.7"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, ānanda, cattāro atthavase sampassamāno pāpabhikkhu saṅghabhedena "
"nandatī”ti."
msgstr "A bad monk sees these four reasons to relish schism in the Saṅgha.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.243:6.8"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
